<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Forcuti</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-19 17:48:45</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Hi all, I've done this quest a few times (I get discouraged and quit during hell levels, sell my EQ agnd firestart another char, but thats a diff story).  Basically you just need to kill shadowmen until gloves drop, which are NOT no rent, so they will stay when you log or go LD, unlink many shadowmen items.  It could be 3 shadowmen, or it could be 100 shadowmen before the gloves drop.  Its not too hard, you get decent exp for them even at 34 and a little at 35.  After getting those gloves (I get them first, they're the hardest), you need to hit cazic thule.  There is a lizard named Radiant that roams the maze, a lot of times a low level group camping the court yard will kill him, and you often hear "Radiant Gloves in CY", in which case just loot them.  Being an enchanter we have an advantage, as all we need is a tank type to come with us, and we can get them ourselves.  Have the tank pull radiant, you'll get a few friends, entrance/enthrall friends, root radiant, and simply blast, loot, and haul ass to the zone which is near.<BR>
<BR>
After that, head to Tarn in highkeep, he's next to the guy that sells bard songs, and is the guy that sells our pet spells.  give him a bloodstone, he gives you another pair of gloves.  Last, go to lavastorm gypsies, there is an enchantress there that you give 50gp to, and she gives you the final pair of gloves.  Go to sol ro, find the dark elf (forget his name), hail him, go through the text, and give him all 4 pairs of gloves.  He then gives you incandescant gloves.<BR>
<BR>
There you go, decent gloves, damn nice AC.<BR>
<BR>
Forcuti<BR>
High Elf Enchantress<BR>
The Nameless<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
